title: DANA GILLESPIE -- Werent Born A Man ( produced by David Bowie )
description:
Dana Gillespie reached a creative high point in the early 1970s
with this album. "Weren't Born a Man".

If some of these tracks sound familiar, it's because part of that album
were on the promo disc I upped the other day that she shared with Bowie.
These are different versions of those songs though.

I haven't gotten her 1974 album yet, but I have a feeling that was Dana's
last album worth listening to.... I downloaded a series of large files
that included all of her albums from 1990 through 2010 and they were
terrible.  All blues music done in the style of the 1930s / 40s -- the kind of
music our grandparents listened to! I think people in their 80s and up might
be her market these days. There was some blues-rock but very little.

It's too bad Dana didn't stick with rock music, because she certainly had
the voice for it! Not so much in recent years though, as her voice
got much deeper.  This album was co-produced by Bowie guitarist Mick Ronson.
